


Building.

    cmake CMakeLists.txt [[-DWITH_UNITY=true|filse][-DWITH_NAUTILUS=true|false][-DGTKVER=2.0|3.0]]
    make
    make [DESTDIR=<destination dir>] install

If unity or/and nautilus is not installed, than
the arguments for cmake a will be ignored.

After installation, you should be run the commands:

This installation new schema to your system 
glib-compile-schemas /usr/share/glib-2.0/schemas 

for installationg new icons to your system
update-icon-cache /usr/share/icons/highcolor
